<paragraph blockId="27.[794,1399,1897,2081]" lastBlockId="28.[189,794,233,289]" lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="91" pageId="27" pageNumber="90">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[794,905,1897,1921]" pageId="27" pageNumber="90">Comment</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="FAUVEL" authorityYear="1905" box="[916,1048,1897,1921]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Amaurodera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="90" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[916,1048,1897,1921]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="90">Amaurodera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
previously included 46 described species distributed in the Oriental and southern East Palaearctic region; for a revised and updated checklist see 
<bibRefCitation author="ASSING, V." box="[794,965,1993,2017]" pageId="27" pageNumber="90" pagination="13 - 111" refId="ref33270" refString="ASSING, V. 2016 b: On some Lomechusini of the Palaearctic and Oriental regions (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Aleocharinae). - Contributions to Entomology 66 (1): 13 - 111 - DOI: 10.21248 / contrib. entomol. 66.1.013 - 111." type="journal article" year="2016">ASSING (2016b)</bibRefCitation>
. Including the newly described species, the genus is now represented by a total of 53 species distributed in the southern East Palaearctic and Oriental regions from 
<collectingCountry box="[332,395,233,257]" name="Nepal" pageId="28" pageNumber="91">Nepal</collectingCountry>
and North 
<collectingCountry box="[518,574,233,257]" name="India" pageId="28" pageNumber="91">India</collectingCountry>
to Sumatra, Borneo, and the 
<collectingCountry box="[275,398,265,289]" name="Philippines" pageId="28" pageNumber="91">Philippines</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
